    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">Understanding the Results</h2>
    <div class="space-y-8">
      <div>
        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Key Metrics Explained:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Monthly Revenue:</strong> Your projected monthly income based on the number of trucks, tows per day, operating days, and fee per tow.</li>
          <li><strong>Monthly Expenses:</strong> The total of all your monthly costs, including loan payments, fuel, insurance, maintenance, and other expenses.</li>
          <li><strong>Monthly Profit:</strong> The difference between your monthly revenue and expenses, representing your business's potential earnings.</li>
          <li><strong>Required Tows to Break Even:</strong> The minimum number of tows needed each month to cover all your expenses.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div>
        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Key Calculations Behind the Tool:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Monthly Revenue Calculation:</strong> 
            <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded">Number of Trucks × Operating Days × Tows Per Day × Fee Per Tow</code>
          </li>
          <li><strong>Loan Payment Calculation:</strong> We use the standard amortization formula to calculate your monthly truck payments:
            <div class="bg-gray-100 p-2 rounded my-2 text-sm overflow-x-auto">
              <code>Monthly Payment = Loan Amount × (Monthly Interest Rate × (1 + Monthly Interest Rate)^Number of Payments) ÷ ((1 + Monthly Interest Rate)^Number of Payments - 1)</code>
            </div>
            Where the loan amount is the truck price minus down payment, and monthly interest rate is the annual rate divided by 12.
          </li>
          <li><strong>Fuel Cost Estimation:</strong> We estimate each truck travels approximately 100 miles per day, and calculate monthly fuel costs as:
            <div class="bg-gray-100 p-2 rounded my-2 text-sm">
              <code>(100 miles ÷ Miles Per Gallon) × Fuel Cost Per Gallon × Operating Days × Number of Trucks</code>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li><strong>Break-Even Analysis:</strong> 
            <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded">Required Tows = Total Monthly Expenses ÷ Fee Per Tow</code>
          </li>
          <li><strong>Growth Projections:</strong> For future months, we apply your specified monthly growth rate using compound growth:
            <div class="bg-gray-100 p-2 rounded my-2 text-sm">
              <code>Future Value = Base Value × (1 + Monthly Growth Rate)^Number of Months</code>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

